grammar_point: な
jlpt: N5
meaning: Do not, Don't (Prohibitive)
meaning_warning: null
details:
  Part of Speech: Sentence Ending Particle
  Register: Standard
  品詞: 助詞
  単語の種類: 終助詞
  使用域: 一般
writeup: な is classified as a sentence ending particle in Japanese. When attached to the base (dictionary)
  form of a verb, it has the nuance of strongly demanding that someone 'not' do something.
examples:
  - japanese: 行くな。
    english: Don't go.
  - japanese: ここでサッカーをするな。
    english: Don't play soccer here.
  - japanese: 泣くな。
    english: Don't cry.
  - japanese: 一人でするな。
    english: Don't do it alone.
  - japanese: 「これは不味い！」って言うな。
    english: Don't say, 'This tastes bad!'
url: https://bunpro.jp/grammar_points/な
false_friends:
  - term: てください
    meaning: Please do (Polite request)
    kind: antonym
  - term: てごらん
    meaning: (Please) try to, (Please) look
    kind: antonym
  - term: なさい
    meaning: Command to do
    kind: antonym
  - term: たまえ
    meaning: (Please) do!, Ask to, Beg to, (Order somebody to do something)
    kind: antonym
  - term: ないでください
    meaning: Please don't (Polite request)
    kind: synonym
  - term: ないで
    meaning: Without doing, Not ~ and ~
    kind: synonym
